description.text:
Cruel Intentions - The Musical
7:15pm Doors | 8pm Show | Ages 13+, minors must be accompanied by parent or legal guardian
Secret Society Seating: $109.00Table Seating: $79.00Bar Area: $49.00
FIRST LOVE IS A BITTERSWEET SYMPHONY.Cruel Intentions: The Musical pulls you into the manipulative world of Manhattan’s most dangerous liaisons: Sebastian Valmont and Kathryn Merteuil. Seduced by revenge and fueled by passion, the two diabolically charming step-siblings place a bet on whether or not Sebastian can deflower their incoming headmaster’s daughter. As the two set out to destroy the innocent girl –and anyone who gets in their way– they find themselves entangled in a web of secrets, temptation, and the cruelest game of all: love.Based on the classic French novel, Les Liaisons Dangereuses, and the sexiest teen drama of all time, this new musical is a full-on ’90s throwback to when email was for “geeks and pedophiles” and rosaries were more than a fashion statement. Featuring your favorite nostalgia-inducing hits like, “Lovefool,” “Just A Girl,” “Only Happy When It Rains,” and, of course, “Bittersweet Symphony.” Don’t miss the most intoxicating musical in Manhattan. Your reputation depends on it.


Refund Policy & Terms of Service: LPR does not issue refunds or exchanges for ticket purchases. All sales are final. No refunds will be processed for unused tickets or for patrons who are denied entry due to not having valid identification for will call pickup or admittance to an age restricted event. Events are subject to change in date, time, reserved seat location or scheduled act at anytime. In the case of an event cancellation, refunds will be provided via the method of payment originally used. Resale of any ticket at a price greater than the original ticket price is absolutely prohibited. We have the right to revoke or reclaim possession of any tickets from the buyer who violates such restrictions.

name.text: Dueling Pianos Musical Sing A Long and Comedy Cabaret
name.html: Dueling Pianos Musical Sing A Long and Comedy Cabaret

description.text:
Dueling Pianos originated in the fabled bars of New Orleans in the 1930s, and spread West across the nation. This exciting, high-energy, all-request entertainment experience has even taken over the Las Vegas strip – and now, Dueling Pianos has found a home in New York City. Imagine the top piano players on the East Coast playing a non-stop, rock-and-roll party where you pick the playlist!
From Billy Joel to Bon Jovi to Britney Spears to Biz Markie, no tune is off-limits. Equal parts concert, comedy and cabaret, you’ll laugh along, dance along and sing along!  Join a group of NYSN members and friends as we spend the night socializing while enjoying the show!

How it works:  The group will meet in front of the venue at 9:30pm sharp.  We will have a special section set aside to sit and enjoy the show. There is a 2 drink minimum  and they will put you on separate checks.
Can I come alone?  Yes 98% of those attending will come on their own. You can also invite friends.
How long does it last?  about 90 minutes.
Dress code?  keep it neat
Non refundable

name.text: Classic Dance Special Event w/ Jerry Geraldo (4 decades of music)
name.html: Classic Dance Special Event w/ Jerry Geraldo (4 decades of music)

description.text:
SPECIAL EVENT: Buy your ticket online now! This will sell out quickly. Get your tickets then remember to show ticket at cashier and say "Jerry Geraldo" at cashier to be directed to the correct event. 
Take a trip back in time to the 70's, 80's, 90's, and 00's considered the best era in music history. Dance and drink to the greatest hits of all time. Michael Jackson, Madonna, George Michael, Whitney Houston all the way to Jennifer Lopez, Ricky Martin and N'sync. Top pop, classic house and freestyle, new wave, classic hip hop and rock and much more!
This may be the most exciting event of the entire year. relive old memories or make brand new ones. Brand new venue with drink specials. 
Event hosted by New York's own Jerry Geraldo with Danielle Redmond and Linda Hawk of the 80's and 90's meetup/social club. Also meet members from the social club and come hang with us!

description.text:
The Hackensack High School Drama Club proudly presents its Spring musical as part of HACPAC's inaugural season.
Cabaret explores the dark, heady, and tumultuous life of Berlin’s natives and expatriates as Germany slowly yields to the emerging Third Reich at the end of the 1920s. Cliff, a young American writer, is immediately taken by English singer Sally Bowles, while Fräulein Schneider, proprietor of Cliff and Sally’s boardinghouse, begins a romance with Herr Schultz, a mild-mannered fruit seller who happens to be Jewish.
Musical numbers include several well-known songs such as “Willkommen,” “Cabaret,” “Maybe This Time” and “Two Ladies.”

name.text: The Revolution Vol. 25: Two Year Anniversary Showcase
name.html: The Revolution Vol. 25: Two Year Anniversary Showcase

description.text:
Doors at 9:30PMAdvance $15  |  At the Door $20
THE REVOLUTION is a performance series highlighting Brooklyn & Harlem based artists + musicians that not only represent the core of independent creativity but who currently stand in the breeding ground of evolution within their genre.
This local musical movement empowers community, change, and activism through performance and unity amongst the arts. Once a month, three different artists showcasing three different genres have a chance to spread love, light, and awareness through their music and their stories. This series supports revolutionary artistry and how important the music is to healing.  
March 2018 marks the Two Year Anniversary of The Revolution Series, founded, curated + produced by Katie Jones. 
To celebrate and recap our journey through the past year, VOL. 25 will feature five incredible live performances from previous artists of the movement:
Dot Cromwell, Beccs, Meridian Lights, Elle Winston, and MAE.SUN.
The Revolution will be sponsored by Radeberger Beer Company, courtesy of RIDER who will be offering $4 tall boys all night long in celebration of the Two Year Anniversary
National Sawdust

description.text:
Shakespeare’s classic comedy Much Ado About Nothing is a timeless story of love interrupted. Join Hamlet Isn’t Dead on a musical vacation to the idyllic Italian countryside where the merrily warring Beatrice and Benedick match their wits and wills. Meanwhile, new couple Claudio and Hero are nearly wrenched asunder by the dastardly villain Don John and his henchmen. But as with all Shakespearean comedies, the truth will out…though not before being comically obstructed by the bumbling sheriff Dogberry.
Hamlet Isn’t Dead’s fresh adaptation of this definitive tale highlights the fun and joy of Much Ado. Come fall in love with Shakespeare again at this festival of laughs and love. Featuring original live music and spirited verse, this is a surefire way to start off the Shakespeare season!

Each evening will open and close with the artists forming a 7 piece band; the inside of the evening will feature them individually. This is a killer night of music you will not want to miss! 

Doors open at 6:30PM / Event at 7:30PM
Advance tickets $11 online. 
Day-of tickets will be $16 at door.
